19using std::string;
20
21Atom::Atom(std::string symbol, const uint16_t z, const uint16_t a, const double abundance, const double mass,
22 const double density)
23 : symbol(std::move(symbol)), z_number(z), a_number(a), abundance(abundance), mass(mass), mass_density(density),
24 number_density(density * N_A * 1.e-24 / mass), // Convert from cm^-3 to Angstroms^-3
25 neutron(getNeutronNoExceptions(z, a))
26{}
27
28Atom::Atom(const Atom &other)
29 : symbol(other.symbol), z_number(other.z_number), a_number(other.a_number), abundance(other.abundance),
30 mass(other.mass), mass_density(other.mass_density), number_density(other.number_density),
31 neutron(getNeutronNoExceptions(other.neutron)) {}
32
33Atom::Atom(const NeutronAtom &neutron)
34 : symbol("user"), z_number(neutron.z_number), a_number(neutron.a_number), abundance(0), mass(0.), mass_density(0.),
35 number_density(0.), neutron(getNeutronNoExceptions(neutron)) {}

3144bool operator==(const Atom &left, const Atom &right) {
3145 if (&left == &right)
3146 return true;
3147
3148 if (left.z_number != right.z_number)
3149 return false;
3150 if (left.a_number != right.a_number)
3151 return false;
3152 if (!AtomEqualsWithNaN(left.abundance, right.abundance))
3153 return false;
3154 if (!AtomEqualsWithNaN(left.mass, right.mass))
3155 return false;
3156 if (!AtomEqualsWithNaN(left.mass_density, right.mass_density))
3157 return false;
3158 if (!AtomEqualsWithNaN(left.number_density, right.number_density))
3159 return false;
3160 if (left.neutron != right.neutron)
3161 return false;
3162
3163 // passes all of the tests
3164 return true;
3165}

3183const Atom &getAtom(const uint16_t z_number, const uint16_t a_number) {
3184
3185 if (z_number > ATOMS.size() || z_number < 1) {
3186 std::stringstream msg;
3187 msg << "Invalid proton number z=" << z_number;
3188 throw std::runtime_error(msg.str());
3189 }
3190
3191 const std::size_t index = z_number - 1;
3192 const auto result = std::lower_bound(ATOMS[index].begin(), ATOMS[index].end(), a_number, compareAtoms);
3193
3194 if (result == ATOMS[index].end() || result->z_number != z_number || result->a_number != a_number) {
3195 std::stringstream msg;
3196 msg << "Failed to find an atom with z=" << z_number << " and a=" << a_number;
3197 throw std::runtime_error(msg.str());
3198 }
3199
3200 return *result;
3201}

3208const Atom &getAtom(const std::string &symbol, const uint16_t a_number) {
3209 // special cases for aliases
3210 if (symbol == "D")
3211 return H2;
3212 if (symbol == "T")
3213 return H3;
3214
3215 // linear search
3216 for (const auto &atom_vec : ATOMS) {
3217 if (!atom_vec.empty() && symbol == atom_vec[0].symbol) {
3218 const auto result = std::lower_bound(atom_vec.begin(), atom_vec.end(), a_number, compareAtoms);
3219 if (result != atom_vec.end()) {
3220 return *result;
3221 }
3222 }
3223 }
3224
3225 // fail loudly
3226 std::stringstream msg;
3227 msg << "Failed to find an atom with symbol=" << symbol << " and a=" << a_number;
3228 throw std::runtime_error(msg.str());
3229}
